    <abstract id="aspace_63c8a7bbf73aea080a56253eb7c8f923">Ronald Vance is an artist and writer active in the United States and Europe during the later half of the 20th century. This collection consists of correspondence, as well as published and unpublished writings by Vance from the late 1960s through the mid 1980s. Works of fiction present in the collection were published in literary journals including <title render="italic">Sun and Moon</title>, <title render="italic">Not Guilty Magazine</title>, and <title render="italic">Interstate Magazine</title>. The collection also includes unpublished writings, including notes and drafts related to Vance's <title render="italic">I Went to Italy and Ate Chocolate</title>.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_afd276b6469a7a78d2cd0e456ac4bc60">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_48ebb40677a34c3f5b10778cbb1b1a23">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection consists of correspondence, as well as published and unpublished writings by Ronald Vance from the late 1960s through the mid 1980s. Works of fiction present in the collection were published in literary journals including <title render="italic">Sun and Moon</title>, <title render="italic">Not Guilty Magazine</title>, and <title render="italic">Interstate Magazine</title>. The collection also includes unpublished writings, including notes and drafts related to Vance's <title render="italic">I Went to Italy and Ate Chocolate</title>.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_1712ded72e6597c76e078205fbdb5c4f">
    <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
<p>Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <arrangement id="aspace_b7bc096a1a825c3c47c629cbc7e7e3dc">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_de7bec5ab1fcc2afeac4a075701d14f5">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Ronald Vance is an artist and writer active during the 1960s through the 1980s. He was born in Connecticut and graduated from Yale University before lecturing on the history of art at Leicester College of Art and then moving to Italy. As of May 2016, he was living in Long Island and was retired.</p>  </bioghist>
  <userestrict id="aspace_9a48833c90e29c5e24c4cc13e2c0ea6d">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>Any rights (including copyright and related rights to publicity and privacy) held by Ronald Vance, were transferred to New York University in 2016 by Ronald Vance. Permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection must be secured from the Fales Library and Special Collections. Please contact fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.</p>  </userestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_6170a1a87ba1c9e9e3361788b04575ec">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Donated by Ronald Vance in May 2016. The accession number associated with this gift is 2016.023.</p>  </acqinfo>
